...MDAs to get 50% Budgetary allocation by end of July. In order to keep strictly to the January – December budget cycle, President Muhammadu Buhari Friday signed into law, the revised N10.81 trillion budget for the year 2020 passed by the National Assembly in June.  At the Budget signing ceremony, President Buhari noted that the budget had to be revised because of the effect of coronavirus on the nation’s economy, while directing all Ministries, department and agencies to ensure effective implementation of the budget and cooperation with the Ministry of Finance, Budget and National planning to achieve the laudable ideas of the budget.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that in view of the recent budget implementation challenges, President Buhari said that the ministries, department and agencies will be given 50 percent of their capital allocation by the end of the month.  Our Correspondent, reports that the signing took place inside the Council Chambers of the State House, Abuja with the Vice-President, Yemi Osinbajo, Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha Chief of Staff to the President, Ibrahim Gambari, Senate President, Ahmed Lawan, Speaker Femi Gbajabiamila and other principal officers witnessing the signing.